{"article_id":"dA0M75p2RtBcN3Qh","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The race for Ohio is slowly tightening ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"but Mitt Romney does not hold a lead in a single poll in the current Real Clear Politics average","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"( he is tied in two ) .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Two polls from Time and CBS/Quinnipiac have grabbed headlines","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"by showing Obama a five-point lead in each .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Romney is chipping away at Obama ' s poll lead ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"but the Democratic advantage in party-ID has increased across these polls .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"When looking at the polls in Ohio ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"it is becoming entirely possible that Mitt Romney should be able to win Ohio","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"without ever showing a consistent lead in the polls , or any lead at all .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"In the past week Romney has trimmed four-tenths of a point off of his deficit in the RCP average ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"going from 2.5 to 2.1 ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"but at the same time , the average party-ID advantage for Democrats in these polls has risen from 5.5 to 6.5 .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"A big reason for the increase in Democrats ' share in the polls is due to early voting .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"If a pollster calls someone","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"who says","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"they voted already ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"they are automatically passed through the likely-voter screen","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"since they have , after all , voted .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"The problem with this can be best summed up by Gregory House :","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"\" Everybody lies . \"","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"Pollsters can only work with what their respondents tell them ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"and this is the reason","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"that likely-voter screens can be so tricky ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"though important , in polling .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"The preferable response is that you are going to vote","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"or , in the case of Ohio , that you ' ve already voted .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Many respondents will say","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"they are going to vote","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"( or have voted )","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"when in fact they may not end up doing it","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"( this effect is known as social-desirability bias ) .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"For this reason , some likely-voter screens ask about previous elections and general political enthusiasm","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"to gauge the actual likelihood","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that a voter will end up in the booth on Election Day .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"But that is where early voting throws the screen out the window","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"if a voter says","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"they voted ,","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"there is nothing","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"a pollster can do to","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"but assume","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"that it ' s true .","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Enter Ohio ,","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"where the current estimates","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"from compiling early in-person and absentee voting","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"shows early turnout to be about 15 percent of voters .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"But responses in the current polls claim","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"that 23 percent of registered voters have already voted .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"That means that polls are overstating early voting by eight percentage points on average .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"This could be in part because some voters have requested an absentee ballot","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"and report","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"that as voting ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"some have mailed in ballots","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"that haven ' t been counted as received yet ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"but some voters are also just flat out saying","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"they voted","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"when they haven ' t .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"It ' s impossible to know the exact reason ,","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"but it ' s clear that more are claiming to vote","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"than really have .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"In the polls ' early-voting results , Obama leads on average by 20 points .","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"There are indications","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"that the GOP has shrunk the Democratic advantage in this category significantly from 2008 ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"but it is unclear how much .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Either way , Obama ' s early-voting advantage gives him a lead","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"that Romney is only scraping away at with his Election Day voter lead .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"if pollsters are finding more respondents","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"who are claiming to have already voted","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"than what the records show ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"some of this early-voter advantage is illusory .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"This is why it is increasingly difficult for Romney to show an lead in the Ohio polls .","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"But","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"even with Obama currently enjoying a 2.1 point lead ,","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"Romney is still in great shape","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"to win Ohio on Election Day .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"Here are some of the reasons for the optimism","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"coming from Boston these days :","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"Romney ' s strength with independents keeps growing :","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"Last week","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"when Obama led the Real Clear Politics average by 2.5 points ,","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"Romney led among independents by an average of 8.7 points .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"Romney has since increased that lead with independents to 12.3 points ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"which is why he ' s been able to cut Obama ' s overall lead","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"even as the polls have leaned more Democratic .","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"In 2008 Obama beat McCain with independents by eight points .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"It would be almost impossible for Obama to win Ohio","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"while suffering a 20-point swing among independents .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"The polls give Democrats a better turnout advantage","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"than they had in 2008 :","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"As I explained in my last Ohio post ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"in 2008 Democrats beat Republicans in turnout by five points .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"The current polls show an average of D+6.6 .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"A D+5 turnout in 2008 gave Obama a 4.5-point victory ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"while he is currently leading by only 2.1 points on an even greater D+6.6 turnout .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"Again , we know","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"it should be very difficult for Democrats to match their 2008 turnout ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"let alone increase it .","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"History suggests","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"late deciders will break against the incumbent :","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"This is a rule","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"that always receives some skepticism ,","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"but it ' s very likely to benefit Romney at least some on Election Day .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"In 2004 , late deciders broke against George W. Bush heavily ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"even though he was a wartime president .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"John Kerry beat Bush by 25 points among voters","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"who decided in the last month ,","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"28 points among voters","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"that decided in the three days prior to Election Day ,","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"and 22 points among day-of deciders .","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"Those voters were 20 percent of the Ohio electorate ;","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"while this year there are expected to be fewer late deciders ,","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Obama can not afford to lose among by those margins","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"and still win .","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"In Ohio , Republicans tend to outperform their share of the national vote :","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"In the last nine elections , the GOP has outperformed in Ohio .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"With Romney currently running just ahead of Obama nationally ,","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"it seems much more likely that Obama ' s lead in Ohio has more to do with the higher party-ID advantage than a dramatic shift in Ohio from the past nine elections .","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"Strength with crossover voters in Ohio :","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"In addition to Romney ' s strength with independents , in the past two elections the GOP candidate has won over more Democrat votes","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"than he ' s lost Republican ones .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"Obama ' s Ohio win in 2008 was based entirely on his strength with independents and the wave turnout ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"both of which are highly unlikely to be repeated in 2012 .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"If Romney wins with independents by anywhere near the current average","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"he has","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"and takes more crossover voters","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"than Obama does ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"Obama would need to exceed 2008 turnout greatly","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"to win .","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"So , with less than two weeks until Election Day we will all know the results soon enough ,","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"but","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"as more Ohio polls come in ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"it is important to remember that the picture for Romney in Ohio is better","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"than many pundits would have us believe .","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"It only takes a quick look at Romney ' s rallies","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"to remind us","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"it ' s not 2008 anymore ,","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"as Republicans have reclaimed the enthusiasm advantage","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"that led to such sweeping 2008 victories for Democrats .","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"That GOP enthusiasm has become contagious since the debates ,","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"and it is exactly what has Team Obama so afraid these days .","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"All","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"they have left","depth":15},{"id":144,"text":"to hang their hopes on","depth":15},{"id":145,"text":"is a slim lead in the polls ,","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"and even that might not be enough on Election Day .","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"- Josh Jordan is a small-business market-research consultant .","depth":2},{"id":148,"text":"You can follow him on Twitter @ Numbersmuncher .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":297,"left":295,"right":296,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":209,"right":294,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":209,"left":161,"right":208,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":155,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":151,"right":154,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":0,"right":150,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":150,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":152,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"par